Sembcorp Industries Ltd. (SCI) , Southeast
Asiaâ€™s biggest utility, said the initial public offering of its
water and power venture in Oman was the largest of the year
there and raised 53 million rials ($138 million).  Sembcorp Salalah shares of the oversubscribed IPO are
expected to start trading on the  Muscat Securities Market  on or
about Oct. 10, the utility said today on its website.  Sembcorp Salalah owns and operates the Salalah Independent
Power & Water Plant. The facility includes a 445-megawatt gas-fired plant and a 69,000 cubic meter a day reverse-osmosis
seawater desalination operation. The plant will provide power
and water under a 15-year purchase agreement with state-owned
Oman Power and Water Procurement Co., Singapore-based Sembcorp
